name: Senach

attributes.attribute: invoked in a magical charm as having control of seven periods of time

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.
text: An Irish goddess named Senach, although obscure, is mentioned in a magical charm for her control over seven periods of time. It is said that she was nurtured by Fairy women, but beyond that not much else is known about her.
